Strike Hulls

Hull Systems (Strike / Light Hull Slot, Passive)

Strike Composite Plating (L1)
Armor Value: +2.25
Hull Points: +22.5
Acceleration: −0.3
Turn Acceleration: −0.75 deg/s²
Cost: 8,000
Durability: 2500 / 2500
Effect: Balanced armor + hull with mild maneuver penalties.
Upgrade Axis: Armor and Hull scale.

Strike Hull Plating (L1)
Hull Points: +45 → +108 (upgrades)
Acceleration: −0.2
Turn Acceleration: −1.0 deg/s²
Cost: 8,000
Durability: 6,000 / 6,000
Effect: Baseline hull module for Strike-class ships that increases maximum Hull Points at the expense of slightly reduced linear acceleration and noticeably reduced turn acceleration. Provides a straightforward survivability boost for fragile Strike hulls without altering Armor Value.
Upgrade Axis: Hull Points scale with item level from +45 at L1 up to +108 at L15. Acceleration and turn-acceleration penalties remain fixed at all levels.

Strike Armor Plating (L1)
Armor Value: +4.5 → +10.8 (upgrades)
Acceleration: −0.4
Turn Acceleration: −0.5 deg/s²
Cost: 8,000
Durability: 6,000 / 6,000
Effect: Strike-class armor module that significantly increases Armor Value while slightly reducing linear acceleration and modestly reducing turn acceleration. Focused on raw damage mitigation rather than extra hull padding.
Upgrade Axis: Armor Value scales with item level from +4.5 at L1 up to +10.8 at L15. Acceleration and turn-acceleration penalties remain fixed at all levels.

Strike HT Plating (L1)
Critical Defense: +7.5 → +18 (upgrades)
Cost: 8,000
Durability: 6,000 / 6,000
Effect: Specialized Strike-class hull module that boosts Critical Defense, reducing the chance and/or severity of incoming critical hits. Does not modify Armor, Hull Points, or maneuvering stats, making it ideal for pilots who want extra protection against burst damage without sacrificing handling.
Upgrade Axis: Critical Defense scales with item level from +7.5 at L1 up to +18 at L15. All other attributes remain fixed at all levels.

Strike Composite Plating (L1)
