Reload: 2.5 s
Power Cost: 9
Firing Arc: 90°
Cost: 175,000
Durability: 18,000 / 18,000
Requirements: Ship class Escort; can only target Capital-class ships.

Effect:
Specialized medium cannon battery that allows an Escort ship (Scythe-only in source game, but treat as “anti-capital” archetype) to directly threaten Capital hulls. High armor piercing and strong per-shot damage balanced by a narrow arc and moderate reload. Should not be usable against Strike/Escort/Line targets in the targeting logic.

Upgrade Model:
Damage scales with level; all other stats remain fixed unless higher-level data indicate changes.

Implementation Notes:

Use normal cannon ballistic model (projectile flight optional or instant-hit, as per engine standard).

Apply standard hit/crit/armor formulas; Capital-only restriction is enforced in target filtering.

Narrow 90° arc encourages deliberate nose-on attack runs or fixed broadside mounts.

Mark internally as “AntiCapitalOnly = true” so AI and UI can clearly communicate its role.

