Line Hulls

Line Hull Plating (L1) – Passive
Hull Points: +350 → +840 (upgrades)
Acceleration: −0.05
Turn Acceleration: −0.2 deg/s²
Cost: 16,000
Durability: 42,000 / 42,000
Effect: Baseline hull module for Line-class ships that substantially increases maximum Hull Points with only minor penalties to linear and turn acceleration. Straightforward durability upgrade for frontline gunships.
Upgrade Axis: Hull Points scale from +350 at L1 up to +840 at L15. Acceleration and turn-acceleration penalties remain fixed.

Line Armor Plating (L1) – Passive
Armor Value: +3.5 → +8.4 (upgrades)
Acceleration: −0.1
Turn Acceleration: −0.1 deg/s²
Cost: 16,000
Durability: 42,000 / 42,000
Effect: Armor-focused plating for Line-class ships that increases Armor Value while modestly reducing both linear and turn acceleration. Emphasizes damage mitigation over maneuverability.
Upgrade Axis: Armor Value scales from +3.5 at L1 to +8.4 at L15. Acceleration and turn-acceleration penalties remain fixed.

Line HT Plating (L1) – Passive
Critical Defense: +7.5 → +18 (upgrades)
Cost: 16,000
Durability: 42,000 / 42,000
Effect: Heavy-tuned hull plating that boosts Critical Defense on Line-class ships, reducing the likelihood and impact of incoming critical hits. Does not affect Armor, Hull Points, or handling.
Upgrade Axis: Critical Defense scales from +7.5 at L1 to +18 at L15. All other stats remain constant.

