Optimal Range: 2750 m (upgrades)
Accuracy: 125
Critical Offense: 100
Reload: 8 s
Power Cost: 64
Firing Arc: 35°
Cost: 500 000
Durability: 20 000 / 20 000

Effect:
High-caliber artillery cannon for Capital-class vessels.
Delivers devastating long-range firepower designed for siege and ship-of-the-line engagements.
Extremely limited firing arc and long reload, balanced by immense per-shot impact and armor penetration.
Incapable of reliably hitting Strike-class ships due to target size and slow traverse.

Upgrade Model:
Increase Damage and Optimal Range per level. Reload and Power Cost remain fixed unless higher-level data show changes.

Implementation Notes:

Uses standard ballistic and crit formulas; apply standard falloff from Optimal Range (peak DPS ≈ 2750 m).

Designed for broadside or fixed forward mounts — do not allow 360° traversal.

Each shot consumes full Power Cost at the moment of firing.

Accuracy tuned for large, slow targets (Line or Capital classes).

Minimum effective range (≈ 2300 m) prevents close-range use; enforce via targeting logic.

Restricted to Capital-class hardpoints — enforce requirement in Store and Fitting UI.

Consider adding screen-shake and concussive sound effects for cinematic impact.

P-01 “Plasma Orb Launcher” — Siege Plasma Projector (L1) – Thorim Only

Damage: 1,000 → 2,200 (upgrades)

Armor Piercing: 55

Range: 1,200 – 4,000 m

Optimal Range: 3,600 m

Accuracy: 150

Critical Offense: 120

Reload: 60 s → 30 s (upgrades)

Power Cost: 100% current energy reserve (requires full energy to arm)

Firing Arc: 30°

Cost: 650,000

Durability: 30,000 / 30,000

Effect:
Thorim-exclusive siege launcher that forms a massive plasma orb from the ship’s entire energy pool.
Fires a slow, devastating projectile capable of crippling Line and Capital hulls but unable to lock onto Strike-class ships.
Energy gating demands meticulous timing — firing drains all energy, disabling active systems until power regenerates.

Upgrade Model:
Damage_min/max scale from 1,000 to 2,200 by L15 while reload drops from 60 s to 30 s.
Range, accuracy, firing arc, and power requirement remain fixed across levels.

Implementation Notes:
Mark as exclusive to the Thorim (ship tag “exclusive:thorim_siege”).
Ensure firing logic verifies the ship is at maximum energy before release and empties the pool on shot execution.
Treat power cost as a full-capacity drain rather than a flat subtraction; boosters doubling energy usage should interact accordingly.
Prohibit targeting Strike-class hulls through weapon AI/validity checks.

